Mishawaka’s Peyton Marshall stretches for more yardage on a run Friday during a game against St. Joseph at the Indians Father Bly Field in South Bend. SBT Photo/GREG SWIERCZ Everything clicks as Cavemen coast past St. Joseph 
Mishawaka’s Greg Burns gets tackled on a sweep by St. Joseph’s Danny Chimutu Friday in South Bend. SBT Photo/GREG SWIERCZ Related Galleries 
The Cavemen head to South Bend to take on St. Joseph Indians. Posted: Saturday, October 3, 2015 6:00 am | Updated: 6:31 am, Sat Oct 3, 2015. Everything clicks as Cavemen coast past St. Joseph By Tom Noie South Bend Tribune SouthBendTribune.com 
SOUTH BEND – Darkness had not even descended on Father Bly Field early Friday evening, yet ninth-ranked (Class 5-A) Mishawaka already had done enough to dominate. 
It started rolling right from the opening kickoff for the Cavemen, who extended their win streak to a season-best three after running away from South Bend St. Joseph, 48-14.
